{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>One of the hallmarks of the terminal stages of apoptosis is internucleosomal DNA breakdown. DNA fragmentation factor (DFF) and endonuclease G (Endo G) are responsible for this process. DFF exists in the nucleus as a heterodimer composed of a 45kDa chaperone and inhibitor subunit (DFF45, also called ICAD-L) and a 40kDa latent nuclease subunit (DFF40/CAD). Apoptotic activation of caspase-3 or -7 results in the cleavage of DFF45 and release of active DFF40 nuclease, which forms homo-oligomers. DFF40's nuclease activity is further activated by proteins such as histone H1, HMGB1/2, and topoisomerase II [[cite:PUB00090023]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false} {"text" "<p>This entry represents DFF45 [[cite:PUB00018568]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure nil, :overlaps-with nil, :member-databases {"pirsf" {"PIRSF037865" "DNA fragmentation factor, alpha subunit"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "DNA fragmentation factor 45", "short" "DFF45"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 0, "domain_architectures" 0, "proteomes" 121, "taxa" 460, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 169, "sets" 0, "proteins" 169, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 121}, "pathways" 2}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR017299", :literature {"PUB00018568" {"URL" nil, "issue" "11", "authors" ["Zhou P" "Lugovskoy AA" "McCarty JS" "Li P" "Wagner G."], "ISO_journal" "Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A.", "DOI_URL" "http://dx.doi.org/10.1073/pnas.111145098", "medline_journal" "Proc Natl Acad Sci U S A", "title" "Solution structure of DFF40 and DFF45 N-terminal domain complex and mutual chaperone activity of DFF40 and DFF45.", "year" 2001, "raw_pages" "6051-5", "volume" "98", "ISBN" nil, "PMID" 11371636}, "PUB00090023" {"URL" nil, "issue" "6", "authors" ["Widlak P" "Garrard WT."], "ISO_journal" "